<title>USA: Borg-Warner Security issues $125 mln debt.</title>
<headline>Borg-Warner Security issues $125 mln debt.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-03-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>The following debt issue from Borg-Warner Security Corp was priced in the 144A private placement market, according to sources.</p>
<p>Borg-Warner Security services include Wells Fargo Armored operations.</p>
<p>Merrill Lynch &amp; Co was lead manager on the deal.</p>
<p>BORROWER BORG-WARNER SECURITY CORP</p>
<p>AMT $125 MLN	 COUPON 9.625 PCT  MATURITY 3/15/2007</p>
<p>TYPE SNR SUB NOTES ISS PRICE 99.334  FIRST PAY DATE 9/15/97</p>
<p>LAST MOODY'S B3    YIELD 9.73 PCT    PAY FREQ SEMI-ANNUAL</p>
<p>LAST S&amp;P B-MINUS   SPREAD 300 BP     CALLABLE NON-CALL FIVE</p>
<p>NOTE: Three-year equity call for 30 percent at par plus coupon ((--U.S. Corporate Bond Unit, 212 859-1672))</p>
</text>
